1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,760
All characters and events in this series are fictional
and created solely for entertainment purposes.
Viewer discretion is advised.

2
00:00:08,280 --> 00:00:10,040
This looks exactly like twins, Jan.

3
00:00:10,040 --> 00:00:11,320
The only difference is the makeup you’re wearing.

4
00:00:11,320 --> 00:00:13,680
Do you think you could get me this actress’s contact information?

5
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:15,640
Be careful.

6
00:00:18,120 --> 00:00:21,440
Sun Atita... is my twin sisters.

7
00:00:22,640 --> 00:00:25,280
(Only I see your light)
Right before we going in, someone handed this to Sun.

8
00:00:25,480 --> 00:00:27,880
So what should we do in this situation, P’Flint?

9
00:00:28,160 --> 00:00:32,200
You’re acting like Sun’s personal bodyguard.

10
00:00:32,439 --> 00:00:33,600
Aren’t you worried about yourself?

11
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:36,640
Someone like me won’t let anyone hurt me that easily.

12
00:00:37,240 --> 00:00:38,200
Let's go home.

13
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:41,600
To me… You aren't just an object.

14
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:46,400
It’s because I’m in love with you, Sun.

15
00:00:48,280 --> 00:00:49,880
Sun… will you be my girlfriend?

16
00:02:10,199 --> 00:02:12,400
I thought you were going to take advantage of me.

17
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:16,440
No, of course not. I was just checking to see if you were awake.

18
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:18,440
So I could go prepare breakfast for you.

19
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:22,400
Playing the role of a good wife already?

20
00:02:22,720 --> 00:02:24,280
P'Flint!

21
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:28,960
If you’re not hungry, then you can let me go. I’m going to take a shower.

22
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:32,360
I won't.

23
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:37,000
P'Flint.

24
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:38,360
No, I won't.

25
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:41,000
Please, let me go.

26
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:44,520
I'm going!

27
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:45,640
Ok, fine.

28
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:54,480
Are you really just going to get up like that?

29
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:56,680
P'Flint!

30
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:01,280
P'Flint!

31
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:59,200
I was just about to go upstairs to call you and let you know breakfast is ready.

32
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:07,040
I knew it. You’re running a fever, Sun.

33
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:09,760
Why don’t you take the day off and get some rest?

34
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:11,760
I’ll call Khun Mooham and let her know.

35
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:14,400
It’s okay, really.

36
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:16,760
I can just come back and rest after I finish work.

37
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:19,040
I’ll be okay.

38
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:32,320
This isn’t what you’d call ‘okay.’

39
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:48,440
Please eat a little, okay?

40
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:52,480
Actually, I can eat by myself. Thank you, P’Flint.

41
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,360
Don’t be stubborn.

42
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:07,080
Do you get dizzy like this often?

43
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:09,800
Do you want me to take you for a check-up?

44
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:11,040
Or...

45
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:13,560
If you don’t want to go to the hospital,

46
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:16,160
I can have a doctor come check on you here instead.

47
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:19,680
Not often. It only happens when I don’t get enough rest.

48
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:22,040
Usually during busy filming periods.

49
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:25,000
Whenever there’s a break, I sneak off to take a nap.

50
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:28,560
If I rest for a bit, I’ll feel better. Then I can get back to work.

51
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:32,080
I'm sorry.

52
00:06:33,880 --> 00:06:35,680
Why are you sorry?

53
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:40,800
About last night,

54
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:43,840
for keeping you up.

55
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:50,000
If you don’t stop teasing me, I’m calling Fey to come stay with me instead.

56
00:06:53,159 --> 00:06:55,159
Just… make sure you rest today, okay?

57
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:58,040
I’ve already called Khun Mooham and told her you’re sick.

58
00:06:59,159 --> 00:07:02,160
And… don’t you have to go to work, P’Flint?

59
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:06,080
How could I go?

60
00:07:06,720 --> 00:07:09,240
My wife is sick.

61
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:15,640
I think Fey should still be free right now.

62
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:18,600
Alright, I’ll stop teasing.

63
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:20,760
Come here.

64
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:22,800
have a little bit, alright?

65
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:29,000
If you're a good girl today…

66
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:31,680
I have a secret to tell you.

67
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:47,440
Why don’t these photos match the concept we planned at all?

68
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:52,159
Please inform the PR team to change the artwork.

69
00:07:52,159 --> 00:07:54,159
Or we can just replace the photographer.

70
00:07:54,159 --> 00:07:55,120
But Khun Fey,

71
00:07:55,440 --> 00:07:57,320
the launch date for this car model is coming up soon.

72
00:07:57,640 --> 00:08:00,440
If we have to redo everything, we might not finish in time.

73
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:01,920
It must be ready.

74
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:06,880
Because our company does not release work that’s imperfect or below standard.

75
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:09,520
Do you understand?

76
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:11,120
Yes. I understand.

77
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:16,080
What are you doing here?

78
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:21,800
There’s something important we need to talk about.

79
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:32,240
What? You want me to model for you… instead of Sun?

80
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:38,240
It’s just that the gallerist really liked the block-shot photos you modeled for.

81
00:08:38,679 --> 00:08:41,240
They said it matches the concept they’ve been looking for.

82
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:44,039
So they’d like you to be the model for this project.

83
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:46,840
Are you kidding me?

84
00:08:47,880 --> 00:08:49,800
I’m not a celebrity like Sun.

85
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:52,120
Besides, using my photos

86
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:54,400
isn’t going to boost their gallery’s reputation.

87
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:57,520
They don’t care who the model is.

88
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:01,200
And besides, the gallery is already well-established.

89
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:05,080
They chose you because you’re right for this project.

90
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:08,600
Do you really think I’m right for it?

91
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:10,800
Yes.

92
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:12,960
I think you’re the right person for this.

93
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:18,960
But if you’re not comfortable, that’s okay.

94
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:20,120
I understand.

95
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:23,520
I’ll have the team draft an apology letter to the gallery.

96
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,680
I’m sorry for disturbing you.

97
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:32,120
And what do I get in return?

98
00:09:37,680 --> 00:09:40,480
I heard you’re looking for a photographer, is that right?

99
00:09:58,960 --> 00:10:01,840
If you keep having work but refuses to go like this…

100
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:04,120
If Fey finds out, she’s going to scold me, you know.

101
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:07,560
Oh? Am I in trouble now?

102
00:10:07,920 --> 00:10:09,480
No.

103
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:10,880
I'm just worried.

104
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:13,320
I’m worried your work might run into problems.

105
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:21,080
Don’t worry, work isn’t a problem.

106
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:24,680
I am.

107
00:10:31,880 --> 00:10:33,000
I think...

108
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:35,560
I’m definitely going to catch your cold.

109
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:39,120
Then… I’ll go get some medicine for you.

110
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,520
I already have some.

111
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:20,520
Thank you.

112
00:11:22,120 --> 00:11:24,240
So… does that mean you’re all better now?

113
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:27,640
Then let’s go check out my secret.

114
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:43,880
Come here.

115
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:55,320
What is this, P’Flint?

116
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:04,720
I decided to buy this place

117
00:12:05,760 --> 00:12:08,800
the moment I found out you were moving here.

118
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:10,600
And now…

119
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:14,720
I don’t think I should keep any more secrets from you.

120
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:19,560
All this time, when I acted cold toward you…

121
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:23,200
it was because I thought that was the right thing to do.

122
00:12:24,080 --> 00:12:26,800
I thought it would help me forget the feelings I have for you.

123
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:31,600
But in the end,

124
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:36,640
it only made me more certain about my feelings.

125
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:44,080
I only said that much, why do you look like you’re about to cry?

126
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:59,160
Thank you so much.

127
00:12:59,560 --> 00:13:01,760
And please make it clear to the media

128
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:05,520
that if there are any more defamatory reports about Sun like this…

129
00:13:05,520 --> 00:13:08,200
We will immediately terminate our sponsorship with that media outlet.

130
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:30,160
Thank you…

131
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:33,760
for everything you’ve done for me.

132
00:13:35,280 --> 00:13:37,760
You don’t have to believe me right now.

133
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:42,120
I have the rest of my life

134
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:45,840
to prove what I’ve said.

135
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:49,560
I love you. Sun.

136
00:13:59,280 --> 00:14:01,280
I love you too. P'Flint.

137
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:42,720
I'm sorry.

138
00:14:56,480 --> 00:14:57,800
Is there something wrong, Khun Mooham?

139
00:14:57,800 --> 00:15:01,440
Um, Khun Rafah… is Sun feeling better now?

140
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:05,560
Senior management at the station has called Sun in for an urgent meeting.

141
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:29,520
You pinned the location of Sun’s dad’s house for me?

142
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:32,440
Are you crazy?

143
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:34,160
That’s a general’s house, damn it!

144
00:15:34,160 --> 00:15:35,280
Think about it

145
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:38,320
what if he thinks we’re scammers

146
00:15:39,640 --> 00:15:41,160
and decides to have us killed?

147
00:15:41,560 --> 00:15:42,960
What are we supposed to do then?

148
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:44,920
Order us killed?

149
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:46,640
Have you been watching too many movies?

150
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:47,960
What?

151
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:51,200
Movies can be based on real stuff, you know!

152
00:15:51,560 --> 00:15:52,880
He’s a general.

153
00:15:59,360 --> 00:16:00,960
I’m seriously asking you

154
00:16:01,160 --> 00:16:02,480
aren’t you scared at all?

155
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:05,520
Or...

156
00:16:06,960 --> 00:16:08,080
You got a plan?

157
00:16:08,920 --> 00:16:09,880
Nope.

158
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:11,360
Nope?

159
00:16:15,160 --> 00:16:16,760
And no, I’m not scared.

160
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:18,720
You’re not scared

161
00:16:21,160 --> 00:16:25,680
but you, of all people… how did you end up coming here with the general’s daughter?

162
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:28,360
Do we look alike?

163
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:48,040
This is a private area, sir. Why did you park your car here?

164
00:16:48,040 --> 00:16:48,880
- This is a private area, sir. Why did you park your car here?
- Uh… I

165
00:16:49,640 --> 00:16:50,760
well…

166
00:16:51,680 --> 00:16:54,560
well… I… I…

167
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:57,840
Is the General here?

168
00:16:58,520 --> 00:17:01,760
Oh! I thought it was someone else. It’s you, Miss Sun.

169
00:17:01,760 --> 00:17:03,040
The General is at home, Young Miss.

170
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:04,800
I’ll escort you inside.

171
00:17:28,720 --> 00:17:29,720
This way, Miss.

172
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:30,800
Thank you.

173
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:37,800
This way, please.

174
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:46,160
Are we about to get killed or what?

175
00:17:46,160 --> 00:17:48,320
Can you please act normal for once?

176
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:55,680
Right this way, Miss.

177
00:18:03,320 --> 00:18:06,640
It’s so complicated… how am I supposed to get out of this?

178
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:11,480
f you don’t stop talking, I’m sending you back to wait in the car.

179
00:18:11,920 --> 00:18:13,920
So now you’re bringing a man home, huh?

180
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:21,920
Hello.

181
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:25,920
Hello.

182
00:18:27,280 --> 00:18:30,640
So your schedule’s finally free these days?
That’s why you have time to come back here, huh?

183
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:33,920
Or do you have some important business with the General?

184
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:34,960
Yes.

185
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:36,760
It’s something important.

186
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:39,200
Something I don’t think I need to explain.

187
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:40,760
Excuse me.

188
00:18:41,280 --> 00:18:43,400
Please inform the security guard for me.

189
00:18:43,680 --> 00:18:47,120
Tell them that any guest
who wishes to see my father must make an appointment in advance.

190
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:51,000
This isn’t a place where outsiders can just walk in and out whenever they please.

191
00:18:53,840 --> 00:18:55,840
As far as I remember,

192
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:59,600
this house is marital property shared by my father and my mother.

193
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:01,680
Even though they’re divorced,

194
00:19:02,080 --> 00:19:05,240
half of the property should rightfully belong to me.

195
00:19:06,800 --> 00:19:09,800
So tell me… who exactly is the outsider here?

196
00:19:13,720 --> 00:19:15,720
Watch what you say. Have some consideration for me.

197
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:17,760
I’m standing right here.

198
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:21,800
I reserve my courtesy and respect for those who deserve it.

199
00:19:23,040 --> 00:19:25,800
If you and your daughter don’t feel that you’ve received any

200
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:28,400
perhaps you should reflect on yourselves.

201
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:29,680
and considered the reason.

202
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:30,480
You!

203
00:19:30,480 --> 00:19:31,680
Sun..

204
00:19:33,960 --> 00:19:35,200
When did you get here, sweetheart?

205
00:19:35,640 --> 00:19:36,600
Just a moment ago.

206
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:41,680
I’m sorry, Dad. I got a little carried away talking with P’Sun.

207
00:19:59,880 --> 00:20:01,200
Hello.

208
00:20:02,480 --> 00:20:03,760
Jan..

209
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:11,560
Jan..

210
00:20:12,680 --> 00:20:14,360
Is it really you?

211
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:17,640
Thank you…

212
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:20,400
for remembering that

213
00:20:21,120 --> 00:20:22,880
you still have another daughter.

214
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:28,520
And I apologize for intruding on your time

215
00:20:28,840 --> 00:20:30,280
without prior notice.

216
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:33,880
As your new wife and her daughter so kindly pointed out.

217
00:20:41,360 --> 00:20:43,080
Why would you say that, Jan?

218
00:20:43,440 --> 00:20:47,440
Normally, if Sun has some free time, he comes by the house all the time.

219
00:20:47,960 --> 00:20:49,040
Never mind.

220
00:20:49,840 --> 00:20:51,280
I came today

221
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:54,080
because I have something important to discuss with you

222
00:20:54,680 --> 00:20:56,560
If possible,

223
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:58,880
I’d like to speak with you in private

224
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:00,880
without any outsiders present.

225
00:21:01,800 --> 00:21:03,640
Would that be convenient for you?

226
00:21:15,960 --> 00:21:17,960
Are you and your mother doing well?

227
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:20,240
I’m doing well,

228
00:21:20,840 --> 00:21:22,120
As for Mother…

229
00:21:23,120 --> 00:21:25,280
she passed away in an accident last year.

230
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:32,800
So, Jan… are you coming back to stay in Thailand?

231
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:35,840
If you need anything, just tell me.

232
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:40,200
When you say ‘take care of me,’

233
00:21:41,160 --> 00:21:44,360
You don’t mean financially like you do with Sun, do you?

234
00:21:45,520 --> 00:21:46,760
Because if that’s the case,

235
00:21:47,600 --> 00:21:49,040
I can take care of myself.

236
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:52,680
Why are you speaking to me so coldly, Chan?

237
00:21:54,160 --> 00:21:56,560
Even though I haven’t been there for you…

238
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:59,000
but

239
00:21:59,320 --> 00:22:01,080
I am still your father.

240
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:05,960
I have always loved my daughter.

241
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:08,800
I do apologize.

242
00:22:09,760 --> 00:22:11,600
But if I’m being honest…

243
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:14,160
I’m just not used to it yet.

244
00:22:14,720 --> 00:22:19,040
And I have to admit… I don’t feel familiar with you.

245
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:25,200
Alright, alright.

246
00:22:26,040 --> 00:22:29,240
Alright. I understand how you feel, Jan.

247
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:33,200
And… you’ve seen your sister, haven’t you? Is that why you stopped by to see me?

248
00:22:34,320 --> 00:22:36,880
So she is my younger sister yes?

249
00:22:40,680 --> 00:22:42,920
In that case, I’ll be on my way.

250
00:22:43,680 --> 00:22:45,480
I only came today

251
00:22:45,840 --> 00:22:48,880
because I needed to know about Sun. Goodbye.

252
00:22:52,640 --> 00:22:53,840
Wait, Jun.

253
00:22:54,360 --> 00:22:56,360
Won’t you stay and have dinner with me?

254
00:23:01,080 --> 00:23:04,280
It might be a good chance to get to know Aunt Mon and Fahsai better.

255
00:23:08,600 --> 00:23:10,200
Get to know them?

256
00:23:11,600 --> 00:23:13,320
I’ve always wondered…

257
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:16,160
why Sun had to move out and live alone in a condo.

258
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:18,800
But what I saw today…

259
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:21,440
gave me quite a few answers.

260
00:23:23,160 --> 00:23:25,400
From now on, I’ll take care of Sun myself.

261
00:23:26,320 --> 00:23:29,040
And I won’t let him get involved with your family again.

262
00:23:31,680 --> 00:23:33,960
And please tell your new wife

263
00:23:34,440 --> 00:23:36,840
that bullying a child does not suit someone of her age.

264
00:23:37,520 --> 00:23:40,760
It doesn’t quite suit the dignity of a General’s wife.

265
00:23:42,360 --> 00:23:45,080
I’ll take my leave now. Goodbye.

266
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:05,960
Oh, where is Sun?

267
00:24:06,920 --> 00:24:08,920
I wonder if she’s okay…

268
00:24:17,640 --> 00:24:18,920
Are you P'Mooham?

269
00:24:18,920 --> 00:24:19,960
Yes.

270
00:24:19,960 --> 00:24:24,240
I’ve just been informed by the senior management that
the meeting will take place in 20 minutes, in the conference room.

271
00:24:24,840 --> 00:24:26,840
Sure thing.

272
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:33,200
Hello? Sun, where are you right now?

273
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:35,680
I’m at the station now.

274
00:24:36,520 --> 00:24:40,720
Okay. I’m not sure what the seniors want to see us about either.

275
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:43,000
But for now, just hurry and get here, okay?

276
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:46,040
We’ll deal with whatever comes up together.

277
00:24:46,040 --> 00:24:48,080
Please hurry, Sun. Come as fast as you can.

278
00:24:48,080 --> 00:24:49,320
Okay.

279
00:24:51,040 --> 00:24:53,680
Earlier this morning, I saw P’Nop meeting with the executives.

280
00:24:54,080 --> 00:24:58,840
It looked like they were discussing the drop in our ship’s popularity
because of the leaked photos of P'Sun.

281
00:24:59,080 --> 00:25:04,480
So I’m thinking the executives probably called her in to evaluate
how to handle the situation.

282
00:25:04,480 --> 00:25:07,320
To bring the ship’s popularity back again.

283
00:25:27,920 --> 00:25:29,000
Are you worried?

284
00:25:34,280 --> 00:25:39,400
P’Mooham called to tell me that
P’Nop went to see the executives at the station this morning.

285
00:25:39,840 --> 00:25:44,520
The reason Sun was called in today
is probably because of the news affecting the ship’s popularity.

286
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:49,240
This time, I have no idea what the executives might ask me and P’Nop to do together.

287
00:25:51,560 --> 00:25:54,280
Do you want me to go in and talk to the executives at the network for you?

288
00:25:55,360 --> 00:25:59,440
It’s okay, P’Flint. I think this is something I need to handle myself.

289
00:26:00,840 --> 00:26:02,440
I’ve made up my mind.

290
00:26:02,840 --> 00:26:04,840
I’m going to be honest with the network about this.

291
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:07,680
don’t want to lie to the fans anymore.

292
00:26:10,680 --> 00:26:16,240
So… does that mean you have to tell them you're already seeing someone?

293
00:26:21,600 --> 00:26:23,600
Look at the way.

294
00:26:36,360 --> 00:26:37,760
Why did you open the window, Win?

295
00:26:37,760 --> 00:26:40,520
So you can breathe. It’ll help you relax.

296
00:27:01,040 --> 00:27:02,240
P'Flint.

297
00:27:04,120 --> 00:27:05,880
Are you okay?

298
00:27:07,480 --> 00:27:08,360
Yes.

299
00:27:23,800 --> 00:27:26,600
I didn’t mean to make you feel uncomfortable.

300
00:27:27,520 --> 00:27:29,920
We cannot deny that the recent news

301
00:27:29,920 --> 00:27:35,600
has damaged both your image and the network’s reputation.

302
00:27:35,600 --> 00:27:39,240
Therefore, the channel believes reviving your pairing with Nop

303
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:42,360
could help overshadow the negative press at this time.

304
00:27:42,800 --> 00:27:45,920
I understand that image is important.

305
00:27:46,160 --> 00:27:50,240
But I have to be honest… I feel uncomfortable pretending

306
00:27:50,240 --> 00:27:54,400
to be paired with P’Nop when it isn’t real.

307
00:27:55,200 --> 00:27:57,880
It makes me feel like I’m lying.

308
00:28:00,240 --> 00:28:01,520
Sun...

309
00:28:01,920 --> 00:28:03,240
Sometimes...

310
00:28:04,720 --> 00:28:08,120
The truth must be presented at the right time and in the right way.

311
00:28:08,920 --> 00:28:10,920
If it’s communicated at the wrong moment,

312
00:28:10,920 --> 00:28:14,440
the consequences could be far worse.

313
00:28:16,560 --> 00:28:21,440
But I believe that if Sun keeps forcing herself
to do something she doesn’t truly want to do,

314
00:28:21,760 --> 00:28:24,640
and the fans eventually notice,

315
00:28:24,840 --> 00:28:29,000
it could damage her image even more in the future.

316
00:28:33,680 --> 00:28:34,600
Acting

317
00:28:35,520 --> 00:28:36,960
is your profession.

318
00:28:37,560 --> 00:28:39,560
You should be able to perform convincingly.

319
00:28:41,160 --> 00:28:45,160
And please don’t forget that the network

320
00:28:45,600 --> 00:28:48,240
has invested a great deal in getting you to where you are today.

321
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:53,200
Most importantly, you still have five years left on your contract.

322
00:28:54,080 --> 00:28:58,880
I sincerely hope we don’t have to escalate this to a legal discussion.

323
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:04,600
Excuse me.

324
00:29:05,760 --> 00:29:09,320
I’ve brought the documents P’Mooham requested.

325
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:21,400
Based on the latest engagement data,
the audience seems to be focusing more on P’Sun’s work itself.

326
00:29:21,600 --> 00:29:25,840
So I was thinking… if we adjust the tone of P’Sun and P’Nop’s pairing

327
00:29:25,840 --> 00:29:32,360
make it less fan-service driven and less overtly romantic,
we might be able to retain a broader fan base.

328
00:29:44,680 --> 00:29:48,560
Thanks for earlier. I didn’t expect you to be that brave.

329
00:29:49,200 --> 00:29:51,200
I’m not that brave, really.

330
00:29:51,200 --> 00:29:56,440
I just felt it wasn’t fair for P’Nop to use the executives to pressure P’Sun like that.

331
00:29:56,800 --> 00:30:00,120
Oh, by the way, what’s your name? Which department are you in?

332
00:30:00,280 --> 00:30:02,840
My name’s Janjao. I’m in PR.

333
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:08,280
Actually, I’m not that good at PR… I think I’d prefer to work in AR.

334
00:30:08,520 --> 00:30:11,040
Then why don’t you intern with P'Mooham? Wouldn’t that be better?

335
00:30:11,560 --> 00:30:12,360
Good.

336
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:14,840
That way, I’ll have a little less on my plate.

337
00:30:15,440 --> 00:30:18,080
I’ll talk to the department head for you.

338
00:30:18,280 --> 00:30:20,920
If they agree, you can start right away.

339
00:30:21,280 --> 00:30:22,920
Thank you very much.

340
00:30:23,200 --> 00:30:24,520
My pleasure.

341
00:30:25,360 --> 00:30:27,440
Then I’ll excuse myself first, P’Mooham.

342
00:30:27,440 --> 00:30:28,360
Okay.

343
00:30:28,360 --> 00:30:29,400
I'll see you.

344
00:30:29,400 --> 00:30:30,480
Make sure you get home safe.

345
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:37,120
Oh? How is P’Sun getting home? I thought you were going to drive her.

346
00:30:38,080 --> 00:30:40,560
Before, yes.

347
00:30:40,720 --> 00:30:44,520
But lately… she has her own ride waiting for her.

348
00:30:45,480 --> 00:30:47,320
Don’t worry. You’ll see for yourself soon.

349
00:30:56,280 --> 00:30:58,360
Weren’t you supposed to be at the wrap party?

350
00:30:59,120 --> 00:31:01,120
Then why are you here dancing all over some guy?

351
00:31:01,360 --> 00:31:04,600
What the hell are you talking about? If you’re drunk, go sleep it off.

352
00:31:22,880 --> 00:31:24,240
How was it?

353
00:31:24,840 --> 00:31:29,320
The network wants me to play up a shipping rumor with P’Nop
to bury the leaked photo scandal.

354
00:31:30,520 --> 00:31:33,720
Luckily, P’Mooham and one of the juniors spoke up for me,

355
00:31:33,720 --> 00:31:36,760
so I don’t have to do joint events with him for now.

356
00:31:38,520 --> 00:31:40,680
But the channel hasn’t completely changed their mind yet.

357
00:31:42,560 --> 00:31:44,960
How long is this going to last?

358
00:31:46,080 --> 00:31:48,480
Probably until my contract runs out.

359
00:31:48,480 --> 00:31:52,160
Or maybe until they find me a new ship partner.

360
00:31:55,800 --> 00:31:57,320
then…

361
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:00,240
Would you be my new ship partner?

362
00:32:03,200 --> 00:32:05,120
Are you still joking around?

363
00:32:06,400 --> 00:32:08,840
Then let’s get going, or we’ll be late.

364
00:32:09,800 --> 00:32:11,360
Where are we going?

365
00:32:13,480 --> 00:32:15,880
I’m taking my future daughter-in-law home… to the Supawaret house.

366
00:32:50,280 --> 00:32:51,360
Let's go.

367
00:33:07,360 --> 00:33:11,040
Why did you bring me to your house, P’Flint? Why didn’t you tell me first?

368
00:33:11,600 --> 00:33:13,320
So I could’ve prepared myself better.

369
00:33:18,680 --> 00:33:21,800
I don’t think you need to prepare anything at all.

370
00:33:22,640 --> 00:33:24,800
You’ve been to my house before.

371
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:26,800
My parents already know you,

372
00:33:27,480 --> 00:33:29,440
so there’s nothing to worry about.

373
00:33:29,440 --> 00:33:31,440
But this time, it’s different.

374
00:33:32,160 --> 00:33:33,560
Different how?

375
00:33:35,320 --> 00:33:39,440
Back then, I came as Fey’s friend.

376
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:41,720
But now…

377
00:33:44,040 --> 00:33:45,800
Why? What about now?

378
00:33:47,640 --> 00:33:49,640
I see…

379
00:33:50,280 --> 00:33:54,240
Because now… you're here as my girlfriend, right?

380
00:33:58,200 --> 00:33:59,560
Whose girlfriend is Sun?

381
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:27,400
Are you mad?

382
00:34:28,159 --> 00:34:29,400
No.

383
00:34:31,120 --> 00:34:35,239
When you’re upset or irritated, you tend to drink something sweet.

384
00:34:35,679 --> 00:34:38,560
Because you said sugar helps lift your mood.

385
00:34:46,440 --> 00:34:47,800
I'm not mad.

386
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:50,040
I’m just a little upset.

387
00:34:50,920 --> 00:34:52,920
You’re my best friend, Sun

388
00:34:53,639 --> 00:34:57,040
I’ve always known you had feelings for her.

389
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:02,280
But my sister… she never showed that she felt the same way you did.

390
00:35:03,040 --> 00:35:06,160
Even though I started to question her’s behavior lately,

391
00:35:06,880 --> 00:35:10,760
I still never thought the two of you would actually end up together.

392
00:35:18,960 --> 00:35:21,680
You and her are both people I love.

393
00:35:23,160 --> 00:35:26,840
I’m just scared that if something goes wrong one day…

394
00:35:27,560 --> 00:35:30,040
I’ll be forced to choose between someone. And I don’t want that.

395
00:35:30,800 --> 00:35:32,800
You understand me?

396
00:35:40,880 --> 00:35:42,600
I’m scared too, Fey.

397
00:35:43,520 --> 00:35:46,200
Everything between me and P’Flint happened so fast…

398
00:35:47,280 --> 00:35:49,440
I barely had time to process it myself.

399
00:35:51,720 --> 00:35:53,880
But the truth is… I love her.

400
00:35:54,840 --> 00:35:57,160
And that’s exactly why I want to give him a chance.

401
00:36:00,720 --> 00:36:02,440
When did this happen?

402
00:36:03,800 --> 00:36:05,040
Last night.

403
00:36:07,560 --> 00:36:09,160
You’re moving in together?

404
00:36:10,640 --> 00:36:11,560
Uh...

405
00:36:12,840 --> 00:36:14,400
So this means...

406
00:36:18,480 --> 00:36:20,840
I have you call you as my sister in law?

407
00:36:21,560 --> 00:36:22,760
Fey.

408
00:36:23,680 --> 00:36:25,600
Hello, my sister in law.

409
00:36:25,600 --> 00:36:26,800
Don't be.

410
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:31,600
Khun Fey, Khun Sun, Khun Phic has asked me to invite you to the dining table.

411
00:36:32,040 --> 00:36:33,320
Okay.

412
00:36:36,080 --> 00:36:38,080
What would you care for this evening?

413
00:36:38,080 --> 00:36:39,160
Oh my god.

414
00:36:44,720 --> 00:36:47,400
Oh, Sun! It’s been such a long time, dear.

415
00:36:48,040 --> 00:36:51,480
Fey, you brought your friend over for dinner and didn’t even tell us?

416
00:36:51,480 --> 00:36:54,120
I would’ve told the maid to cook more if I’d known.

417
00:36:55,440 --> 00:36:57,840
Good evening.

418
00:36:58,560 --> 00:36:59,640
How are you?

419
00:37:00,240 --> 00:37:03,400
I’m doing well, dear. And how have you been, Sun?

420
00:37:04,200 --> 00:37:10,200
Fey, you brought Sun at just the right time.
Flint’s bringing a girlfriend home to introduce her today.

421
00:37:10,200 --> 00:37:13,320
I was actually hoping you and Sun could help me… screen her a little.

422
00:37:15,440 --> 00:37:17,440
I’ve already screened her carefully, Mom.

423
00:37:17,920 --> 00:37:22,120
The only thing you should worry about… is Flint breaking her heart.

424
00:37:23,960 --> 00:37:27,000
Flint, what time is your girlfriend coming?

425
00:37:28,200 --> 00:37:29,280
She's here.

426
00:37:30,400 --> 00:37:33,600
Then hurry up and bring her to meet your mother and me.

427
00:37:34,480 --> 00:37:35,360
That’s right, dear.

428
00:37:36,080 --> 00:37:37,040
Sure thing.

429
00:37:42,960 --> 00:37:45,040
Sun, could you introduce yourself again?

430
00:37:52,280 --> 00:37:55,280
Good evening again, Mr. and Mrs. Suphawaret.

431
00:37:55,960 --> 00:37:57,800
I’m…

432
00:37:58,360 --> 00:37:59,800
My girlfriend.

433
00:38:06,840 --> 00:38:10,480
Do you believe me now that I screened her well?

434
00:38:14,120 --> 00:38:16,960
Well then, now that everyone’s here, shall we start dinner?

435
00:38:17,560 --> 00:38:18,960
Wait, Dad.

436
00:38:20,280 --> 00:38:23,880
I remember when you were little, you loved stir-fried vegetables.

437
00:38:23,880 --> 00:38:26,280
I’ll have the maid prepare some for you, dear.

438
00:38:27,320 --> 00:38:28,680
Thank you so much.

439
00:38:29,400 --> 00:38:30,400
Come here, dear

440
00:38:31,280 --> 00:38:32,720
Sun, sit next to me.

441
00:38:39,360 --> 00:38:43,960
How about we take a family photo? It’s not often that we’re all together like this.

442
00:38:44,680 --> 00:38:49,080
And this is the first time P'Flint’s ever brought her girlfriend home.

443
00:38:49,080 --> 00:38:52,040
You could say this is a historic moment.

444
00:38:59,200 --> 00:39:02,280
One. Two. Three.

445
00:39:25,640 --> 00:39:27,640
What are you thinking about, P’Flint?

446
00:39:28,080 --> 00:39:29,640
Is something wrong?

447
00:39:31,400 --> 00:39:32,560
Nothing.

448
00:39:33,360 --> 00:39:35,280
I was just thinking…

449
00:39:36,440 --> 00:39:39,360
“Atita Supawaret” has a nice ring to it.

450
00:39:40,240 --> 00:39:41,680
Do you want to change it already?

451
00:39:42,160 --> 00:39:43,480
P'Flint.

452
00:39:45,920 --> 00:39:47,200
All set, P’Flint.

453
00:39:48,760 --> 00:39:50,680
All set? What do you mean, Fey?

454
00:39:57,920 --> 00:39:59,320
P'Flint.

455
00:39:59,600 --> 00:40:01,600
I just got called in by the network today…

456
00:40:03,160 --> 00:40:05,320
And now you post something like that?

457
00:40:05,800 --> 00:40:07,800
It’s going to trend for a whole week, for sure.

458
00:40:08,480 --> 00:40:10,320
I’m giving you a whole month.

459
00:40:10,320 --> 00:40:17,320
“Famous actress and the most sought-after businesswoman who’s never been seen
in a family photo with any other woman before.”

460
00:40:17,720 --> 00:40:19,360
It’s definitely going to be the talk of the town.

461
00:40:20,400 --> 00:40:22,400
We’re launching a new on-screen couple.

462
00:40:37,160 --> 00:40:38,760
I’m sorry, P’Mooham…

463
00:40:38,760 --> 00:40:39,880
Sorry? For what?

464
00:40:40,320 --> 00:40:43,440
Don’t tell me… the person in that clip is you, Sun?

465
00:40:44,080 --> 00:40:45,520
What clip?

466
00:40:45,800 --> 00:40:49,360
The one where you were all over some guy at a club.

467
00:40:49,960 --> 00:40:52,440
It’s being shared everywhere right now.

468
00:40:52,760 --> 00:40:53,920
Wait, what?

469
00:40:54,280 --> 00:40:58,280
I’m at P’Flint’s house right now.

470
00:40:58,440 --> 00:41:01,480
How could there be a leaked clip of me at a club? And why does it look like that?

471
00:41:01,480 --> 00:41:03,880
This time, the video is pretty clear.

472
00:41:04,880 --> 00:41:07,600
I’ll send it to you so you can see for yourself.

473
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:09,160
Okay.

474
00:41:17,560 --> 00:41:18,960
Where is this place?

475
00:41:19,400 --> 00:41:24,240
Could it be the same place Khun Peach said she saw you before?

476
00:41:32,040 --> 00:41:34,800
Are you at the same club from the video right now, Sun?

477
00:41:34,800 --> 00:41:37,080
If that’s true, this is only going to get worse.

478
00:41:37,720 --> 00:41:42,720
Don’t worry, P’Mooham. I’m here with P’Flint and Fey too.

479
00:41:43,600 --> 00:41:46,520
The moment you went public, you’ve been glued to each other ever since, huh?

480
00:41:47,520 --> 00:41:49,160
Have you seen the photos already, P’Mooham?

481
00:41:49,160 --> 00:41:51,680
Oh please, it’s not just me.

482
00:41:51,680 --> 00:41:55,800
Right now, executives and reporters won’t stop calling.

483
00:41:55,800 --> 00:42:00,960
If there’s nothing urgent, I’ll call you back from my other phone.

484
00:42:00,960 --> 00:42:04,840
I need this one to handle all these incoming calls.

485
00:42:07,120 --> 00:42:09,280
Did P’Sun really go to that club?

486
00:42:10,120 --> 00:42:12,200
What are we going to do if the reporters find out?

487
00:42:15,400 --> 00:42:18,440
I’m praying no one finds out either.

488
00:42:22,400 --> 00:42:24,200
Good evening P'Peach.

489
00:42:24,520 --> 00:42:26,520
Thank you for coming to help.

490
00:42:26,880 --> 00:42:28,280
It's my pleasure.

491
00:42:28,640 --> 00:42:31,040
Sun, you’ve never actually been here before, right?

492
00:42:31,600 --> 00:42:33,040
Never. Not once.

493
00:42:33,280 --> 00:42:36,800
When you said you saw me, I was surprised too.

494
00:42:37,520 --> 00:42:41,640
Um… maybe we should go inside and look around first?

495
00:42:41,640 --> 00:42:43,640
I think we should split up and search separately.

496
00:42:43,640 --> 00:42:45,400
Besides… I’ve been here before.

497
00:42:47,000 --> 00:42:48,280
You come with me, Sun.

498
00:42:51,840 --> 00:42:52,720
I’m coming too.

499
00:42:52,720 --> 00:42:54,080
Wait.

500
00:42:54,560 --> 00:42:58,080
I came all the way here to help you.
Are you seriously going to leave me behind like this?

501
00:43:01,080 --> 00:43:03,080
Come on. Let's go.

502
00:43:03,600 --> 00:43:04,720
Hey.

503
00:43:06,360 --> 00:43:07,760
I can walk myself.

504
00:43:18,160 --> 00:43:20,400
With this many people… are we even going to find anything?

505
00:43:24,600 --> 00:43:26,000
Are you okay?

506
00:43:26,800 --> 00:43:28,040
Yes.

507
00:43:28,040 --> 00:43:29,400
It's okay.

508
00:43:29,400 --> 00:43:30,560
I’ll check this area.

509
00:43:30,560 --> 00:43:33,800
You take the front of the stage.

510
00:43:34,520 --> 00:43:36,000
You’ll be okay on your own, right?

511
00:43:36,720 --> 00:43:38,720
I can take care of myself.

512
00:43:40,840 --> 00:43:42,440
A martini, please.

513
00:43:54,720 --> 00:43:56,040
Why is this so bitter?

514
00:43:57,160 --> 00:43:58,600
I should’ve ordered a mocktail instead.

515
00:44:02,880 --> 00:44:04,560
You’re Khun Paabfah, aren’t you?

516
00:44:04,560 --> 00:44:05,920
Yes?

517
00:44:05,920 --> 00:44:07,160
It's you.

518
00:44:07,160 --> 00:44:09,480
I didn’t expect to run into you here, Khun Paabfah.

519
00:44:11,960 --> 00:44:14,400
Do we know each other?

520
00:44:15,200 --> 00:44:22,920
Welcome, everyone, to “Black or White: What’s Your Status?”

521
00:44:22,920 --> 00:44:24,480
Black or White.

522
00:44:26,000 --> 00:44:26,960
Yes.

523
00:44:27,240 --> 00:44:29,240
If you’re single, wear white.

524
00:44:29,240 --> 00:44:31,240
If you’re taken, wear black.

525
00:44:34,160 --> 00:44:37,640
In that case… shall we get to know each other better?

526
00:44:45,040 --> 00:44:48,680
I hope you’ll do me the honor, Khun Paabfah.

527
00:45:08,240 --> 00:45:09,680
Let's go.

528
00:45:14,240 --> 00:45:16,840
Shouldn’t you ask for Khun Paabfah’s consent first?

529
00:45:18,080 --> 00:45:19,480
The way you’re doing this…

530
00:45:20,520 --> 00:45:22,680
it’s quite disrespectful, don’t you think?

531
00:45:23,760 --> 00:45:25,000
Hey, you.

532
00:45:56,320 --> 00:45:58,040
Is that clear enough?

533
00:46:25,160 --> 00:46:27,160
P’Flint, maybe you should change your shirt first?

534
00:46:36,640 --> 00:46:38,480
What if someone recognizes you?

535
00:46:39,080 --> 00:46:41,080
Should you pull my cap down a little lower?

536
00:46:44,600 --> 00:46:46,160
Excuse me.

537
00:46:49,360 --> 00:46:51,080
Are you here alone?

538
00:46:52,400 --> 00:46:54,600
I noticed you’re wearing...

539
00:46:54,600 --> 00:46:55,800
white.

540
00:46:59,280 --> 00:47:00,920
but I’m already taken.

541
00:47:00,920 --> 00:47:01,800
Sorry.

542
00:47:02,280 --> 00:47:03,720
Oh… I see.

543
00:47:10,000 --> 00:47:12,040
Maybe we should check over there instead?

544
00:47:20,280 --> 00:47:22,280
P’Sun? It’s me, Janjao.

545
00:47:22,640 --> 00:47:24,400
Are you still at the club?

546
00:47:24,440 --> 00:47:26,520
Yes. Why? Is something wrong?

547
00:47:26,960 --> 00:47:29,720
Right now on X, a fan account posted that…

548
00:47:29,960 --> 00:47:31,920
if anyone can take a photo proving

549
00:47:31,920 --> 00:47:33,920
that the person in the leaked clip is really you,

550
00:47:33,920 --> 00:47:35,800
they’ll give out 100,000 baht as a reward.

551
00:47:36,160 --> 00:47:38,720
I think you should leave right now, P’Sun.

552
00:47:43,640 --> 00:47:45,120
What’s going on?

553
00:47:45,720 --> 00:47:48,040
Someone posted a 100,000-baht reward

554
00:47:48,040 --> 00:47:50,720
for anyone who can take a photo proving that I am here.

555
00:48:16,800 --> 00:48:18,400
Can I not leave just yet?

556
00:48:19,280 --> 00:48:23,120
If someone sees you here, it’ll only confirm

557
00:48:23,600 --> 00:48:25,000
that the person in the clip is really you.

558
00:48:26,320 --> 00:48:29,440
But I need to know who that woman is, P’Flint.

559
00:48:30,760 --> 00:48:32,760
This might be my only chance

560
00:48:32,760 --> 00:48:33,920
to find her.

561
00:48:37,280 --> 00:48:39,960
I won’t let anyone misunderstand you ever again.

562
00:48:41,040 --> 00:48:42,920
Come back to the room with me.

563
00:48:47,200 --> 00:48:49,120
Are you looking for me?

564
00:49:40,680 --> 00:49:42,320
Dear, Diary.

565
00:49:42,320 --> 00:49:44,320
I’m about to finish writing in you.

566
00:49:44,640 --> 00:49:46,640
Time for you to go into my suitcase,

567
00:49:47,160 --> 00:49:49,480
because you’re coming back to Thailand with me.

568
00:49:50,440 --> 00:49:52,440
I don’t know…

569
00:49:52,840 --> 00:49:54,960
if the person I miss over there misses me too.

570
00:49:55,640 --> 00:49:57,560
miss me or not.

571
00:49:58,040 --> 00:50:00,800
She's never even asked Fey to pass along a message for me.

572
00:50:01,520 --> 00:50:03,280
But I just want her to know…

573
00:50:03,640 --> 00:50:05,640
That I miss you.

574
00:50:07,720 --> 00:50:09,000
I'm Jan.

575
00:50:09,600 --> 00:50:11,600
I'm your twin sisters.

576
00:50:13,160 --> 00:50:14,680
There’s something I need to talk to you about.

577
00:50:14,680 --> 00:50:16,080
About me kissing you?

578
00:50:16,080 --> 00:50:17,800
Why are you making that face?

579
00:50:17,800 --> 00:50:20,920
Are you afraid I’ll tell my sister about it?

580
00:50:23,240 --> 00:50:25,240
There’s something I need to confess to you, Sun.

581
00:50:27,920 --> 00:50:29,120
Are you free next week?

582
00:50:29,120 --> 00:50:29,520
Why?

583
00:50:29,840 --> 00:50:33,240
Well… you kissed me earlier. So I assumed you’d want to take responsibility.

584
00:50:34,280 --> 00:50:35,800
How many times do I have to tell you?

585
00:50:36,160 --> 00:50:37,440
I didn’t kiss you.

586
00:50:37,920 --> 00:50:41,080
Please. Anyone who saw that would call it a kiss.

587
00:50:41,800 --> 00:50:44,960
Hello, Ms. Rafah. There’s a package addressed to you.

588
00:50:46,360 --> 00:50:51,400
It looks like whoever took these photos… was very close to you and Sun.

589
00:50:57,440 --> 00:51:00,720
(You're mine.)
